Table.name: REQ_PART
Table.commentInRDBMS: Materiel Request Part List: This entity lists all of the parts that are required in a particular materiel request. Parts can be requested in the form of a BOM part (allows for alternates), or an explicit part number. Once a particular inventory item has been selected to fulfill this materiel request, the inventory record can be assigned to this list.

Column.name: REQ_PRIORITY_DB_ID
Column.commentInRDBMS: FK REF_REQ_PRIORITY. Every part request has a priority. This priority is used to indicate which requests are more important, and should be dealt with first.

Column.name: REQ_PRIORITY_CD
Column.commentInRDBMS: FK REF_REQ_PRIORITY. Every part request has a priority. This priority is used to indicate which requests are more important, and should be dealt with first.

Column.name: PO_PART_NO_DB_ID

Column.name: PO_PART_NO_ID

Column.name: REQ_BOM_PART_DB_ID
Column.commentInRDBMS: FK to EQP_BOM_PART. The requested bom part. By specifying a BOM part instead of a specific part number, you are requesting one from a list of alternate parts.

Column.name: REQ_BOM_PART_ID
Column.commentInRDBMS: FK to EQP_BOM_PART. The requested bom part. By specifying a BOM part instead of a specific part number, you are requesting one from a list of alternate parts.

Column.name: REQ_SPEC_PART_NO_DB_ID

Column.name: REQ_SPEC_PART_NO_ID

Column.name: REQ_MASTER_ID
Column.commentInRDBMS: Master id of the part request. Groups part requests together under the original part request id that was split by Maintenix.

Column.name: REQ_QT

Column.name: EST_ARRIVAL_DT

Column.name: REQ_NOTE

Column.name: REQ_TASK_SDESC
Column.commentInRDBMS: If this is an ad-hoc part request, then this column will allow you to enter a freeform task reference. This field is data only, and will not be used for any logic.

Column.name: LOCK_RESERVE_BOOL
Column.commentInRDBMS: In certain situations, you will want to lock the reservation of an inventory item against a part request. When an inventory reservation is locked, Maintenix will never try to break this link during the auto-reservation

Column.name: LAST_AUTO_RSRV_DT
Column.commentInRDBMS: This field stores the last date/time that the autoreservation logic ran for the part request.

Column.name: ASSIGN_HR_ID

Column.name: ALT_ID
Column.commentInRDBMS:
The alternate key is useful for identifying a specific row in the database when dealing with integrations and Maintenix front ends. The alternate key can is unique to each entity and acts as a surrogate key.

The alternate key is intended to be system generated.

Column.name: SUPPLY_CHAIN_DB_ID
Column.commentInRDBMS: FK REF_SUPPLY_CHAIN. This is a link to the supply chain for this request.

Column.name: SUPPLY_CHAIN_CD
Column.commentInRDBMS: FK REF_SUPPLY_CHAIN. This is a link to the supply chain for this request.

Column.name: UPDATED_ETA
Column.commentInRDBMS: The estimated time of arrival of the part to the organization's network. This is set manually by the material controller so that the line planner can schedule the work. Not to be confused with EST_ARRIVAL_DATE, which is calculated by Maintenix, but not always available or accurate.

Column.name: DELIVERY_NOTE
Column.commentInRDBMS: A note about the delivery ofthe part to the organization's network. This is set manually by the material controller so that the line planner can schedule the work.

Column.name: QTY_UNIT_DB_ID
Column.commentInRDBMS: The db_id of the unit of measure for the part request quantity.

Column.name: QTY_UNIT_CD
Column.commentInRDBMS: The code of the unit of measure for the part request quantity

Column.name: RSTAT_CD
Column.commentInRDBMS: A physical attribute that defines the read/write access of the record.

Column.name: CREATION_DT
Column.commentInRDBMS: The database server's timestamp captured at the time the record was inserted.

Column.name: REVISION_DT
Column.commentInRDBMS: The database server's timestamp captured at the time the record was last updated.

Column.name: REVISION_DB_ID
Column.commentInRDBMS: The database identifer (MIM_LOCAL_DB) captured at the time the record was last updated. Identifies where modifications are being made in distributed Maintenix.

Column.name: REVISION_USER
Column.commentInRDBMS: The user that last modified the record. The user is either a) the user that logged into Maintenix - pushed into the database from the client or b) if the record update is not via a Maintenix application, the user is the Oracle user name that is processing the transaction.

Column.name: PRINTED_DT
Column.commentInRDBMS: The date that a part request issue transfer was last printed.
